; `(comptime (sizeof …))` — the tree-walk interpreter has no sizeof/alignof/offsetof,
; but the COMPILED comptime engine does (interp deletion step 1, mac-8): the site is
; routed through real codegen and folds to the literal 8, so this now BUILDS (exit 0).
; The pre-mac-8 seed's interpreter still errors here (exit 1) — a regression tripwire.
(defn main [] (-> :i64) (comptime (sizeof :i64)))
